The paper discusses block codes for Gaussian channels with feedback, which is a topic in information theory and communication systems. Therefore, cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.COMM (Communications and Networking) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also mentions the use of Gaussian random variables and channels, which are common in signal processing and statistical inference, suggesting that cs.SI (Signal Processing) and cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) are also possible sub-categories. Finally, the paper discusses the performance of the proposed scheme in terms of error probability, which is a metric commonly used in data science and machine learning, indicating that cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) could also be a relevant sub-category.
